# Migrations & jOOQ Conventions

## Adding a migration

1. Create `src/main/resources/db/migration/V{n}__{description}.sql` (increment version)
2. Regenerate jOOQ types (offline — no live DB needed):
   ```bash
   source /usr/local/sdkman/bin/sdkman-init.sh && ./gradlew jooqCodegen
   ```
3. Commit both the migration file and the regenerated `src/main/generated/` sources

Flyway runs automatically on app startup. It is disabled in the test profile via `%test.quarkus.flyway.migrate-at-start=false`.

## jOOQ setup

- Uses `DDLDatabase` — reads migration SQL files via an in-memory H2 instance, no live DB required
- Generated package: `com.chriswininger.db.generated`
- `DSLContext` is produced by `com.chriswininger.db.DSLContextProducer` (CDI `@ApplicationScoped` producer backed by `AgroalDataSource`)
- There is NO `quarkus-jooq` extension — jOOQ is wired manually via the producer

## Repository pattern

- One `@ApplicationScoped` repository per table in `com.chriswininger.repository`
- Inject `DSLContext dsl` and use generated `Tables.*` constants and typed `*Record` classes

## Postgres-specific DDL in migrations

Wrap any syntax the jOOQ parser doesn't understand (e.g. `CREATE EXTENSION`) to avoid codegen failures:

```sql
-- [jooq ignore start]
CREATE EXTENSION postgis;
-- [jooq ignore stop]
```

## Type notes

- `TEXT[]` columns are generated as `String[]` — correct for Postgres at runtime
- `TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE` is generated as `OffsetDateTime`
